**Summary:** Juliana is the more skilled interrogator by a significant margin. Her scene (p-bd327c, p-def3ab, p-d3a506 in cynewulf-juliana-9a2157 ch. 1) is a genuine multi-round cross-examination: she physically holds the demon, sets the agenda, and drives successive disclosures until she has extracted a complete taxonomy of demonic method and history. The demon himself testifies that no human has ever bound him so effectively. Andreas's confrontations with the Mermedonian devil (p-51b3f4, p-ca8f6e in cynewulf-andreas-07b573 ch. 1) are powerful acts of defiant witness and theological proclamation, but his mode is declaration rather than interrogation — the demon asks, he answers. The ontological gap in Juliana's scene closes from below; in Andreas's, it is endured but never reversed.
